        <abstract> 
<p>Communicates two cases of inheritance reported by J. P. Bishop [in <hi rend="doubleUnderline">13137</hi>]. The work of E. Brown-Séquard has demonstrated that effects of injuries can be inherited ["Hereditary transmission of an epileptiform affection accidentally produced", <hi rend="italic">Proc. R. Soc. Lond.</hi> 10 (1860): 297–8]. E. Dupuy has sent CD a still more remarkable case.</p> 
        </abstract>
